Special thanks to thn81, L42y, City-Busz, and all of the other AUR maintainers that helped make it possible to run Unity under Arch Linux!

Please make sure you don't already have modified versions of the dependencies installed. For example, gtk3-ubuntu might fail to compile if there's a modified version of gtk3 already installed.

Packages ending with "-ubuntu" contain Ubuntu patches and REPLACE Arch Linux versions of those packages.

Order to compile/install:

01: glib2-ubuntu                   -> glib 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
02: gtk2-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
03: gtk3-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 3.0 with Ubuntu patches
04: qt-ubuntu                      -> Qt toolkit with Ubuntu patches
05: gconf-ubuntu                   -> A configuration database system
06: libdbusmenu                    -> Library for passing menus over DBus
07: libindicator                   -> Symbols and functions for indicators
08: libindicate                    -> Libraries for apps to raise 'flags' on DBus
09: libindicate-qt                 -> Qt bindings for libindicate
10: libappindicator                -> Library to export menu bar to Unity
11: appmenu-gtk                    -> Application menu module for GTK+
12: bamf                           -> Application matching framework
13: libqtbamf                      -> Qt bindings for bamf
14: libqtdee                       -> Qt binding and QML plugin for Dee
15: libqtgconf                     -> Qt bindings for GConf
16: dconf-qt                       -> Qt bindings for DConf
17: sni-qt                         -> Turns Qt tray icons into appindicators
18: ido                            -> Widgets and objects used for indicators
19: libzeitgeist                   -> Client library to interact with Zeitgeist
20: zeitgeist-datahub              -> Plugins that insert events into Zeitgeist
21: python2-geoclue                -> Geoclue Python module
22: python2-xapian                 -> Python bindings for Xapian
23: zeitgeist-extensions           -> Extensions for Zeitgeist
24: activity-log-manager           -> Blacklist configuration GUI for Zeitgeist
25: gsettings-desktop-schemas-ubuntu -> Shared GSettings schemas for the desktop
26: gnome-settings-daemon-ubuntu   -> Daemon handling the GNOME session settings
27: gnome-session-ubuntu           -> GNOME Session Manager
28: pulseaudio-ubuntu              -> A featureful, general-purpose sound server
29: gnome-control-center-ubuntu    -> Utilities to configure the GNOME desktop
30: gnome-screensaver-ubuntu       -> Screensaver and screen locking for GNOME
31: metacity-ubuntu                -> Lightweight GTK+ window manager
32: launchpad-integration          -> Launchpad.net integration
33: indicator-applet               -> GNOME panel indicator applet
34: indicator-application          -> Takes menus and puts then in the panel
35: indicator-appmenu              -> An indicator to host the menus from apps
36: libtimezonemap                 -> GTK+3 timezone map widget
37: indicator-datetime             -> A very, very simple clock
38: indicator-messages             -> Collects messages that need a response
39: indicator-multiload            -> Port of the GNOME multiload applet
40: indicator-power                -> Indicator to show battery information
41: indicator-session              -> Indicator to manage session
42: indicator-sound                -> A unified sound menu
43: network-manager-applet-ubuntu  -> Network Manager applet with indicator support
44: gnome-bluetooth-ubuntu         -> Gnome bluetooth applet with indicator support
45: gtest                          -> C++ testing utility based on xUnit
46: gmock                          -> A library for writing C++ mock classes
47: overlay-scrollbar *            -> Overlay scrollbars for GTK 2 and GTK 3
48: plasma-widget-menubar *        -> KDE Plasma widget to display menubar
49: xfce4-indicator-plugin *       -> XFCE panel plugin to display indicators
50: utouch-evemu                   -> Event emulation for the uTouch stack
51: utouch-frame                   -> Touch frame library
52: fixesproto-ubuntu              -> X11 Fixes extension wire protocol
53: libxfixes-ubuntu               -> X11 misc. 'fixes' extension library
54: xorg-server-ubuntu             -> Xorg X server
55: check                          -> Unit testing framework for C
56: utouch-grail                   -> Gesture recognition and instantiation lib.
57: utouch-geis                    -> Implementation of the GEIS interface
58: nux                            -> An OpenGL toolkit
59: unity-asset-pool               -> Design assets for Unity
60: gnome-menus2                   -> Gnome menu specifications
61: libunity                       -> Library for integrating Unity
62: libunity-misc                  -> Differently licensed stuff for Unity
63: nautilus-ubuntu                -> File manager and graphics shell for GNOME
64: unity-lens-applications        -> Unity applications lens
65: unity-lens-files               -> Unity files lens
66: unity-lens-music               -> Unity music lens
67: unity-lens-video               -> Unity video lens
68: compiz-core-ubuntu             -> Compiz core components
69: libcompizconfig-ubuntu         -> Compiz configuration system library
70: compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu -> GConf backend for Compiz
71: compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu * -> KConfig4 backend for Compiz
72: compizconfig-python-ubuntu     -> Compizconfig bindings for Python
73: ccsm-ubuntu                    -> Compiz configuration manager
74: compiz-plugins-main-ubuntu     -> Compiz main plugins
75: compiz-plugins-extra-ubuntu    -> Compiz extra plugins
76: libgdu                         -> GNOME Disk Utility library
77: unity-core *                   -> Parts of Unity 3D needed for Unity 2D
78: unity                          -> A desktop experience designed for efficiency
79: unity-2d                       -> 2D implementation of Unity

* Optional packages
  - overlay-scrollbar              => For GNOME/Unity users who want a space saving scrollbar
  - plasma-widget-menubar          => For KDE users who want a global menubar
  - xfce4-indicator-plugin         => Ayatana indicators plugin for the XFCE panel
  - compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in GConf
  - compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in KConfig4
  - unity-core                     => For users that want Unity 2D, but not Unity 3D

All of PKGBUILD's were checked by namcap for consistency. The binary packages have not been checked yet.

Troubleshooting:

Global menus aren't working when logging in with KDM (KDE display manager).

  This happens because previous versions of KDM weren't patched to source the
  /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc.d/ directory. This is fixed in kdebase-workspace version
  4.7.2-1, but requires the KDM configuration files to be regenerated (resetting
  all KDM configuration options). To regenerate the configuration files, run as root

    # rm -rvf /usr/share/config/kdm
    # genkdmconf

AHH! Something is wrong with Unity!

  Try resetting the settings for Unity and Compiz and relogin:

    $ rm -rvf ~/.compiz-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.cache/compizconfig-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.config/compiz-1/
    $ gconftool-2 --recursive-unset /apps/compiz-1
    $ gconftool-2 --recursive-unset /apps/compizconfig-1
    $ rm -rvf ~/.gconf/apps/compiz-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.gconf/apps/compizconfig-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.cache/unity/
    $ rm -vf ~/.cache/unity-lens-video

  If something is still wrong, please file a bug report at either:

    https://github.com/chenxiaolong/Unity-for-Arch/issues

  or

    https://bugs.launchpad.net/unity-for-arch

I have an ATI graphics card that needs the AMD Catalyst/fglrx driver.

  Use the xorg-server-ubuntu-1.11 package instead of xorg-server-ubuntu.
